Making a tomato spinach sausage pasta recipe is quick, easy, and uses budget-friendly ingredients. Perfect for lunch or dinner, it will only take you 30 minutes to prepare the dish. Here are a few tips to make the best sausage pasta ever. Ingredients Preparation Step 1 Prepare the pasta by boiling then set it aside. Step 2 While the pasta is cooking, saut√© the sausage meat then add the garlic and a drizzle of vegetable oil. Cook until fragrant and the sausage meat is no longer pink. Step 3 Add chopped tomatoes to the sausage mixture with a sprinkling of paprika and cayenne pepper. Step 4 Once those have cooked nicely, stir in the tomato puree and add the spinach, letting it wilt. Step 5 Drain excess water from the pasta before adding it to the sausage, tomato, and spinach sauce. Mix gently before serving it hot with a cold beverage on the side.